31:18.374 --> 31:21.357
In 1973, the U.S. congress

31:21.377 --> 31:23.859
passed a new farm subsidy bill.

31:23.879 --> 31:26.862
Among other things, it
included incentives

31:26.882 --> 31:30.366
that encouraged a massive
increase in corn production.

31:30.386 --> 31:33.369
One of the major byproducts
of this enormous corn surplus

31:33.389 --> 31:37.873
was a low-cost sweetener called
"high fructose corn syrup".

31:37.893 --> 31:39.875
Companies could add this
sweetener to anything

31:39.895 --> 31:41.377
from soda pop to hot dogs,

31:41.397 --> 31:45.881
and then make these products
widely available at low prices.

31:45.901 --> 31:48.384
Processed sugars and
other refined foods

31:48.404 --> 31:49.885
are far more calorie-dense

31:49.905 --> 31:51.887
than the whole plants
they're made from.

31:51.907 --> 31:53.889
The dramatic increase
in their use

31:53.909 --> 31:57.393
is a major reason why our
food has become richer.

31:57.413 --> 32:00.896
To evolutionary psychologist
and author Dr. Doug Lisle,

32:00.916 --> 32:02.398
the consumption of
unnaturally dense foods

32:02.418 --> 32:06.402
is the main cause for the
epidemic of obesity in America.

32:06.422 --> 32:08.904
It isn't that people have
become more self-indulgent.

32:08.924 --> 32:12.408
It isn't because they're
lazier than they ever were.

32:12.428 --> 32:14.910
What's happening is that their
mechanisms of satiation

32:14.930 --> 32:16.412
are being fooled.

32:16.432 --> 32:17.913
The process starts

32:17.933 --> 32:18.914
with a range of receptors
in our stomachs

32:18.934 --> 32:21.917
that help us gauge how
much food we've eaten.

32:21.937 --> 32:24.420
These include stretch
receptors to help measure

32:24.440 --> 32:26.922
the sheer volume of
food in our stomachs.

32:26.942 --> 32:29.425
We also have density receptors,

32:29.445 --> 32:31.427
to help determine the
caloric density,

32:31.447 --> 32:35.431
or what we more commonly call
the richness of our food.

32:35.451 --> 32:38.934
For instance, 500 calories
of natural plant food

32:38.954 --> 32:40.455
fills the stomach completely,

32:40.956 --> 32:43.939
triggering both our stretch
and density receptors

32:43.959 --> 32:46.942
to signal our brain that
we've had enough to eat.

32:46.962 --> 32:50.446
But 500 calories of unnaturally
rich or processed food

32:50.466 --> 32:52.948
fills the stomach far less,

32:52.968 --> 32:54.950
deceiving these receptors
into telling our brain

32:54.970 --> 32:56.471
that we need to eat more.

32:56.972 --> 32:59.474
Even worse is 500
calories of oil,

32:59.975 --> 33:01.457
which is almost pure fat

33:01.477 --> 33:04.460
and barely triggers
any response at all.

33:04.480 --> 33:06.462
The problem with weight
management in humans

33:06.482 --> 33:08.964
is that if you make these
foods completely artificial,

33:08.984 --> 33:10.466
which we do today,

33:10.486 --> 33:13.469
you wind up with a problem
that people have to overeat

33:13.489 --> 33:14.970
just to be satisfied.

33:14.990 --> 33:16.972
But why do these
concentrated foods

33:16.992 --> 33:20.476
that are so harmful to us
give us so much pleasure?

33:20.496 --> 33:22.478
Dr. Lisle says the
answer is related

33:22.498 --> 33:25.981
to a system called the
motivational triad.

33:26.001 --> 33:28.003
This is a trio of
biological mechanisms

33:28.504 --> 33:30.986
that nature has designed
into every creature on earth

33:31.006 --> 33:32.488
so they can survive
to pass their genes

33:32.508 --> 33:34.990
on to the next generation.

33:35.010 --> 33:37.012
The first leg of the
motivational triad

33:37.513 --> 33:39.495
is pleasure seeking.

33:39.515 --> 33:42.498
And, primarily, two things
are the cause of that,

33:42.518 --> 33:45.000
and those two things
are food and sex.

33:45.020 --> 33:46.502
So in the case of a
great white shark,

33:46.522 --> 33:50.005
its basically got a neon sign
flashing across its forehead

33:50.025 --> 33:53.008
saying, "food, sex,
food, sex, food, sex."

33:53.028 --> 33:55.511
Unless it's a male, then it
says, "sex, food, sex, food,"

33:55.531 --> 33:57.513
but it's pretty much
the same thing.

33:57.533 --> 34:00.015
The other two legs of
the motivational triad

34:00.035 --> 34:01.517
are avoiding pain

34:01.537 --> 34:04.520
and doing everything with
the least amount of effort.

34:04.540 --> 34:06.522
Pleasure seeking,
pain avoidance,

34:06.542 --> 34:07.523
and energy conservation,

34:07.543 --> 34:09.525
that really sums up
animal behavior,

34:09.545 --> 34:12.027
whether we're talking about a
paramecium under a microscope

34:12.047 --> 34:13.529
or a great white shark.

34:13.549 --> 34:16.532
Richer foods naturally
excite our senses

34:16.552 --> 34:18.033
because it's nature's
way of telling us

34:18.053 --> 34:20.554
they will provide the highest
amount of dietary reward

34:21.056 --> 34:24.039
with the least amount of effort.

34:24.059 --> 34:26.542
This helped our ancestors
find the most calorie-dense

34:26.562 --> 34:27.543
and ripe foods available,

34:27.563 --> 34:32.047
which contributed
to our survival.

34:32.067 --> 34:33.047
But in today's environment,

34:33.068 --> 34:35.551
we can artificially
increase calorie density

34:35.571 --> 34:39.054
well beyond what our ancestors
would have found in nature.

34:39.074 --> 34:42.077
The resulting foods give us a
hyper-normal amount of pleasure,

34:42.578 --> 34:44.059
leading us into something

34:44.079 --> 34:47.062
Dr. Lisle calls the
pleasure trap.

34:47.081 --> 34:50.065
What the pleasure trap
is is an interaction

34:50.085 --> 34:52.568
between our natural instincts,

34:52.588 --> 34:54.570
which are trying to tell
us the right thing to do,

34:54.590 --> 34:57.092
and some kind of artificial,
modern stimulation

34:57.593 --> 35:00.596
that is piggybacking or
hijacking that process.

35:01.096 --> 35:02.597
So the classic example
of the pleasure trap

35:03.098 --> 35:05.581
would be drugs and
drug addiction.

35:05.601 --> 35:09.084
The way drugs work
is they hijack

35:09.104 --> 35:11.106
the existing pleasure circuits.

35:11.607 --> 35:14.089
When certain chemicals
hit those areas,

35:14.109 --> 35:16.611
they cause feelings of
euphoria and excitement.

35:17.112 --> 35:19.094
The same drug-like
effect happens

35:19.114 --> 35:22.617
when we eat highly
concentrated, processed foods.

35:23.118 --> 35:25.100
We've removed the fiber,
we've removed the water,

35:25.120 --> 35:26.621
we've removed the minerals.

35:27.122 --> 35:28.103
We've done everything
that we can

35:28.123 --> 35:31.106
to hyper-concentrate
sugar and fat

35:31.126 --> 35:33.108
and add a bunch of salt
as well into the food,

35:33.128 --> 35:34.610
and now what the food has become

35:34.630 --> 35:36.612
is it's become a
low-grade addiction.

35:36.632 --> 35:38.614
These things are drugs.

35:38.634 --> 35:40.616
They have other
deleterious side effects,

35:40.636 --> 35:43.619
not the least of which is
adding a lot of empty calories.

