If it walked, hopped,
swam, crawled, slithered,

35:57.152 --> 36:00.636
had eyes, a mom and a dad...
don't eat it.

36:00.656 --> 36:02.157
Dr. Mason contends

36:02.658 --> 36:04.660
that the less affluent
segments of our population

36:05.160 --> 36:07.643
have difficulty making
the best food choices.

36:07.663 --> 36:09.645
Well, first of all,

36:09.665 --> 36:13.649
the diets are calorie-rich
and nutrient-poor.

36:13.669 --> 36:15.651
This is the real problem.

36:15.671 --> 36:19.655
And, unfortunately, poor
people are poor in everything.

36:19.675 --> 36:22.658
They're poor in health,
they're poor in food choices,

36:22.678 --> 36:26.662
they're poor in almost every
aspect that you could think of.

36:26.682 --> 36:28.163
This makes the less prosperous

36:28.183 --> 36:30.666
particularly vulnerable to
the low-grade addiction

36:30.686 --> 36:33.168
of highly processed foods.

36:33.188 --> 36:34.670
People want stuff that's fast,

36:34.690 --> 36:36.672
people want stuff that's quick,

36:36.692 --> 36:39.174
and they like the
stuff that's salty,

36:39.194 --> 36:41.677
and they like the taste
of something fried.

36:41.697 --> 36:43.679
And so those are the
kinds of things

36:43.699 --> 36:46.201
that you see in our community.

36:58.213 --> 37:01.196
San'dera Nation lives
in a quiet suburb

37:01.216 --> 37:03.699
in Cleveland, Ohio,
with her five children.

37:03.719 --> 37:08.704
In October 2008, she was
stricken by a strange illness.

37:08.724 --> 37:11.707
I wanna say something,
but it's not coming out.

37:11.727 --> 37:14.209
I'm getting really
shaky and sweats,

37:14.229 --> 37:15.711
and then I'm cold and I'm sick

37:15.731 --> 37:17.713
and I'm fatigued, and my
stomach hurts and everything.

37:17.733 --> 37:19.214
So I went to the doctor,

37:19.234 --> 37:24.219
and that's when he diagnosed me
with hypertension and diabetes.

37:24.239 --> 37:25.740
Like Joey Aucoin,

37:26.241 --> 37:29.725
San'dera was treated with
expensive prescription drugs.

37:29.745 --> 37:32.227
I was in denial for a while.

37:32.247 --> 37:35.731
I heard what they said, but
I was in denial, like, mmm.

37:35.751 --> 37:38.253
I still ate things
I shouldn't have.

37:38.754 --> 37:39.735
I didn't really
get the education

37:39.755 --> 37:41.737
that I needed to know,

37:41.757 --> 37:45.240
so I really depended on
that pill to save me.

37:45.260 --> 37:47.743
Then San'dera met with
Dr. Esselstyn,

37:47.763 --> 37:50.245
who recommended that she
treat her illnesses

37:50.265 --> 37:52.748
with a whole foods,
plant-based diet.

37:52.768 --> 37:54.750
Come on in, and
we'll get to work.

37:54.770 --> 38:00.255
I was a little nervous, but
he made it real easy for me.

38:00.275 --> 38:02.758
I was real interested
in what he had to say

38:02.778 --> 38:03.779
and what he was
going to teach me

38:04.279 --> 38:07.282
and the new journey that I
would be taking with him.

38:28.804 --> 38:30.786
Between China and the
United States...

38:30.806 --> 38:33.288
In 1974, Chinese
premier zhou enlai

38:33.308 --> 38:37.292
was hospitalized
with bladder cancer.

38:37.312 --> 38:39.795
Knowing that his
disease was terminal,

38:39.815 --> 38:40.796
he decided to give his country

38:40.816 --> 38:43.799
a more complete
understanding of cancer.

38:43.819 --> 38:45.300
So he initiated
what would become

38:45.320 --> 38:47.302
one of the largest
and most thorough

38:47.322 --> 38:50.305
scientific studies in history.

38:50.325 --> 38:54.309
650,000 researchers catalogued
the mortality patterns

38:54.329 --> 38:55.811
caused by several
types of cancer

38:55.831 --> 39:01.316
for the years between
1973 and 1975.

39:01.336 --> 39:03.819
The study encompassed
every county in China

39:03.839 --> 39:07.342
and over 880 million people.

39:07.843 --> 39:12.327
Zhou died in 1976, years
before his study was complete.

39:12.347 --> 39:15.330
Okay, and you'll need
how many shirts?

39:15.350 --> 39:17.833
Probably three?

39:17.853 --> 39:19.835
- Yeah.
- Okay.

39:19.855 --> 39:20.836
Zhou enlai's cancer study

39:20.856 --> 39:22.838
would ultimately
have a major impact

39:22.858 --> 39:25.340
on what Dr. Campbell himself
has called

39:25.360 --> 39:27.862
the capstone of his research.

39:31.867 --> 39:33.348
Early 1980.

39:33.368 --> 39:34.850
And you were there for
two or three months?

39:34.870 --> 39:37.853
Dr. Junshi Chen is now
senior research Professor

39:37.873 --> 39:41.356
with the Chinese center for
disease control and prevention.

39:41.376 --> 39:43.859
He first met Dr. Campbell
at Cornell in 1980,

39:43.879 --> 39:45.861
when he was a member of
the Chinese Institute

39:45.881 --> 39:48.884
of Food and Nutrition Science.

39:49.384 --> 39:51.366
The cold war was just
beginning to thaw,

39:51.386 --> 39:54.369
and Dr. Chen was among the
first senior scientists

39:54.389 --> 39:56.872
from China to visit
the United States.

39:56.892 --> 39:58.874
By then, Dr. Campbell had become

39:58.894 --> 39:59.875
one of the most distinguished

39:59.895 --> 40:02.377
nutritional biochemists
in the world.

40:02.397 --> 40:04.880
When they discovered this book,

40:04.900 --> 40:08.383
a significant
collaboration was born.

40:08.403 --> 40:13.388
This is the atlas of
cancer mortality in China.

40:13.408 --> 40:16.892
Published in 1981,
the cancer atlas

40:16.912 --> 40:20.395
was the result of Zhou
Enlai's nationwide study.

40:20.415 --> 40:23.918
It showed a highly unusual
geographical distribution

40:24.419 --> 40:26.401
of different types
of cancer in China,

40:26.421 --> 40:30.906
which tended to be clustered
in certain hot spots.

40:30.926 --> 40:33.929
The same was true with
cancer after cancer.

40:34.429 --> 40:35.911
And the counties with
the highest levels

40:35.931 --> 40:36.932
were often far greater

40:37.432 --> 40:39.414
than the counties with
the lowest levels.

40:39.434 --> 40:42.918
So, for example,
esophageal cancer,

40:42.938 --> 40:44.920
according to this cancer map,

40:44.940 --> 40:48.924
the mortality has a
400-fold difference

40:48.944 --> 40:52.928
among different
counties in China.

40:52.948 --> 40:53.929
- That's huge.
- Yeah.

40:53.949 --> 40:57.432
And in...
I understood, in the United States,

40:57.452 --> 41:00.936
only several-fold difference.
Not even...

41:00.956 --> 41:03.438
maybe twofold or so, we see.

41:03.458 --> 41:06.942
Yeah, yeah.
So that caught our attention

41:06.962 --> 41:09.945
in term of, so, why?

41:09.965 --> 41:12.447
Because they're all Chinese.

41:12.467 --> 41:13.949
Genetically, they
are all the same.

41:13.969 --> 41:17.953
And the why they have
so much difference

41:17.973 --> 41:20.956
in single cancer mortality?

41:20.976 --> 41:24.960
So we believe it has to be
related to the environment.

41:24.980 --> 41:27.462
The bigger environment.

41:27.482 --> 41:29.984
And from our professional
perspective,

41:30.485 --> 41:32.987
of course, it's
diet and nutrition.

41:33.488 --> 41:34.970
Dr. Chen and I said, you know,

41:34.990 --> 41:37.472
"why don't we just go
there and do a study?"

41:37.492 --> 41:39.474
For Dr. Campbell,

41:39.494 --> 41:41.977
it was the opportunity
he'd been looking for.

41:41.997 --> 41:44.980
Among other things, he could
examine how his observations

41:45.000 --> 41:47.482
about liver cancer
in Filipino children

41:47.502 --> 41:49.985
and the findings
from his lab studies

41:50.005 --> 41:53.008
applied to a large
human population.

41:53.508 --> 41:54.990
The project would consider

41:55.010 --> 41:58.493
367 diet and
health-related variables,

41:58.513 --> 42:00.495
making it one of
the most ambitious

42:00.515 --> 42:03.999
nutritional studies
ever conceived.

42:04.019 --> 42:05.000
Dr. Campbell and his associates

42:05.020 --> 42:09.004
carefully chose 65 counties
scattered across China.

42:09.024 --> 42:11.506
These counties were
mainly located in rural

42:11.526 --> 42:13.508
or semi-rural areas.

42:13.528 --> 42:16.011
We used the rural counties

42:16.031 --> 42:19.514
because they are stable
in their residents,

42:19.534 --> 42:22.017
and they have been
in this lifestyle

42:22.037 --> 42:25.520
for at least 20 to 30 years.

42:25.540 --> 42:27.522
More than 350 workers
were trained.

42:27.542 --> 42:31.026
They carefully surveyed
the diet and lifestyle

42:31.046 --> 42:35.530
of 6,500 people in
the chosen counties.

42:35.550 --> 42:39.534
Urine and blood samples
were also taken.

42:39.554 --> 42:44.039
In 1983, doctors Campbell,
chen, and their collaborators

42:44.059 --> 42:47.042
began to analyze the vast
amount of information

42:47.062 --> 42:48.543
that had been collected.

42:48.563 --> 42:51.065
The job would take years.

