Nothing fits.
I gotta go shopping.

43:36.111 --> 43:38.593
It's just everything,
all my clothes.

43:38.613 --> 43:40.595
A good problem to have.

43:40.615 --> 43:41.596
It's been fun for him,

43:41.616 --> 43:43.098
because I think he's learned

43:43.118 --> 43:45.600
in addition to the fact that
he's seeing such great results,

43:45.620 --> 43:48.603
that it's...He loves it.

43:48.623 --> 43:50.105
I don't think he'll go
back to his old ways.

43:50.125 --> 43:53.108
He feels too good, and he likes...

43:53.128 --> 43:55.110
even if he started to
go off a little bit,

43:55.130 --> 43:58.113
he feels too good, his energy's
too good, he looks younger.

43:58.133 --> 43:59.614
And the fact that he
would have to go back

43:59.634 --> 44:02.117
on all the meds, you
know, if he did,

44:02.137 --> 44:04.119
I think that that's
a huge motivation

44:04.139 --> 44:07.142
for him to maintain
the lifestyle.

44:11.646 --> 44:15.630
In the mid-1980s, Dr. Caldwell Esselstyn

44:15.650 --> 44:17.132
was struggling to
organize a study

44:17.152 --> 44:19.634
on coronary artery disease.

44:19.654 --> 44:21.636
His plan was to put
a group of patients

44:21.656 --> 44:23.638
on a diet of low-fat
plant-based foods,

44:23.658 --> 44:27.142
along with small quantities
of low-fat dairy products

44:27.162 --> 44:31.646
and minimal amounts of
cholesterol reducing drugs.

44:31.666 --> 44:34.649
And slowly over the
next, uh, 18 months,

44:34.669 --> 44:37.152
I got the 24 patients
that I had asked for.

44:37.172 --> 44:38.653
But the ones they sent me

44:38.673 --> 44:41.656
Were a little bit sicker
than I had thought.

44:41.676 --> 44:42.677
These were patients
who had failed

44:43.178 --> 44:45.160
their first or second
bypass operation.

44:45.180 --> 44:47.662
They had failed their first
or second angioplasty.

44:47.682 --> 44:49.164
And there were
five who were told

44:49.184 --> 44:50.665
by their expert cardiologists

44:50.685 --> 44:52.167
they would not
live out the year.

44:52.187 --> 44:54.689
One of the most
gravely ill patients

44:55.190 --> 44:57.672
was a 59-year-old speech and
communications teacher,

44:57.692 --> 44:59.674
Evelyn oswick.

44:59.694 --> 45:02.177
Ate all the chocolate
candy I could eat,

45:02.197 --> 45:04.679
ate every doughnut I
could put my hands on.

45:04.699 --> 45:06.681
Oh, I just love
things like that,

45:06.701 --> 45:08.183
a lot of gravy.

45:08.203 --> 45:10.685
And then, um, I had my...

45:10.705 --> 45:13.688
I have had two heart attacks
before I met Dr. Esselstyn.

45:13.708 --> 45:16.691
When I had the
second heart attack,

45:16.711 --> 45:20.195
the doctor said that I
should prepare for death,

45:20.215 --> 45:21.696
really is what he said.

45:21.716 --> 45:23.198
And I looked at him and I said,

45:23.218 --> 45:26.201
"do you really mean that
what you want me to do

45:26.221 --> 45:27.222
"is buy a rocking chair

45:27.722 --> 45:29.204
and just sit there and
rock away and wait?"

45:29.224 --> 45:31.206
And he just looked
at me and he said,

45:31.226 --> 45:33.728
"yes, that's just exactly
what I'm saying."

45:37.732 --> 45:42.217
Anthony Yen was born
and raised in China.

45:42.237 --> 45:46.221
And we were eating a typical
Chinese cultural diet.

45:46.241 --> 45:49.724
A very small piece of meat.

45:49.744 --> 45:54.729
But they sliced it, and so
it was cooked for flavor

45:54.749 --> 45:56.231
rather than your American style,

45:56.251 --> 45:59.734
when you eat, you eat a large,
great, big piece of meat,

45:59.754 --> 46:03.738
which you could easily fed
the whole family in China.

46:03.758 --> 46:06.260
And we eat a lot of
vegetables in China.

46:06.761 --> 46:07.742
And we had soup.

46:07.762 --> 46:09.263
But once I came to
the United States,

46:09.764 --> 46:13.748
you find beginning to
experience fast food.

46:13.768 --> 46:17.752
The hamburgers and
cheeseburgers, pizza.

46:17.772 --> 46:19.754
And I noticed my weight
beginning to gain.

46:19.774 --> 46:22.757
When Mr. Yen was 56 years old,

46:22.777 --> 46:26.261
he suddenly experienced
severe chest pains.

46:26.281 --> 46:30.265
At that point in time, I
had a open heart surgery.

46:30.285 --> 46:34.269
I have five bypass... five.

46:34.289 --> 46:36.771
But it was very interesting.

46:36.791 --> 46:40.275
About a week later, uh,

46:40.295 --> 46:43.778
I felt my chest
tighten up again.

46:43.798 --> 46:49.284
So myself and my wife went
to see Dr. Esselstyn.

46:49.304 --> 46:52.787
I saw every one of
these patients myself

46:52.807 --> 46:55.290
every two weeks for
the first five years.

46:55.310 --> 46:57.792
And at that visit, we would get

46:57.812 --> 47:00.295
a full cholesterol
lipid profile.

47:00.315 --> 47:03.298
We would get blood
pressure, weight,

47:03.318 --> 47:05.300
and I would go over
every morsel they ate.

47:05.320 --> 47:07.302
By using simple foods

47:07.322 --> 47:09.804
as the main treatment
for his patients,

47:09.824 --> 47:13.828
Dr. Esselstyn was bucking a
high-tech, high-cost system

47:14.329 --> 47:15.810
that was deeply entrenched
in both big medicine

47:15.830 --> 47:17.812
and big government.

47:17.832 --> 47:19.814
You know, behind my back,

47:19.834 --> 47:22.317
I got to be known as Dr. Sprouts.

47:22.337 --> 47:26.341
But I guess I've always
liked a challenge.

47:28.843 --> 47:31.826
We preheated the oven,
got the water going.

47:31.846 --> 47:33.347
I just added some seasonings.

47:33.848 --> 47:35.830
And then we add the
onions and the spinach.

47:35.850 --> 47:38.333
I've never been a morning
person, my whole life.

47:38.353 --> 47:42.837
And, uh, but previous
to this experience,

47:42.857 --> 47:47.342
um, it had probably
been worse than ever.

47:47.362 --> 47:51.846
And that entailed needing
to get up in the morning

47:51.866 --> 47:54.349
and caffeinate myself

47:54.369 --> 47:56.851
with cokes and red bulls
and stuff like that,

47:56.871 --> 48:00.355
uh, before I could even
think or start to work.

48:00.375 --> 48:02.357
We didn't make the rice noodles,

48:02.377 --> 48:04.859
but you can just
boil them real quick

48:04.879 --> 48:06.361
and then throw this
on top of them.

48:06.381 --> 48:07.862
Right, right.

48:07.882 --> 48:09.864
He's actually eating more often,

48:09.884 --> 48:12.867
but he's eating the right
foods, and he lost weight.

48:12.887 --> 48:15.870
So he certainly feels
much better that way.

48:15.890 --> 48:18.392
And you can tell it in
his face, in his neck,

48:18.893 --> 48:19.874
you know, in his belly.

48:19.894 --> 48:21.876
It's all...
he's lost a lot of weight there.

48:21.896 --> 48:23.378
He also has a better energy.

48:23.398 --> 48:24.879
Um, he's waking up earlier now.

48:24.899 --> 48:27.882
That's great, because we have
then some morning time together.

48:27.902 --> 48:30.385
I don't have to carry anything.

48:30.405 --> 48:31.886
You're the doctor.

48:36.411 --> 48:37.892
1990.

48:37.912 --> 48:40.895
Following nearly a decade
of intense effort,

48:40.915 --> 48:42.897
Dr. Campbell and his colleagues

48:42.917 --> 48:44.899
finally publish
their China study.

48:44.919 --> 48:48.903
It identified no less
than 94,000 correlations

48:48.923 --> 48:50.905
between diet and disease.

48:50.925 --> 48:53.408
Those are big numbers
for any study.

48:53.428 --> 48:54.909
And in the end of the day,

48:54.929 --> 48:57.412
when we did all these
correlations in this book here,

48:57.432 --> 48:58.913
and we looked at
the number of them

48:58.933 --> 49:00.915
that were statistically
significant,

49:00.935 --> 49:03.918
it was between about
8,000 to 9,000.

49:03.938 --> 49:05.420
When you have that large
number of correlations

49:05.440 --> 49:08.423
then you start
analyzing each one,

49:08.443 --> 49:10.425
if it works out as
statistically significant,

49:10.445 --> 49:12.427
this means that if 19 out of 20

49:12.447 --> 49:14.429
are pointing in the
same direction,

49:14.449 --> 49:16.431
it's highly significant

49:16.451 --> 49:18.933
and likely to be true.

49:18.953 --> 49:20.935
Hundreds of detailed
tables and charts

49:20.955 --> 49:22.437
were included in the study.

49:22.457 --> 49:25.940
Each one presented the raw
data that was collected.

49:25.960 --> 49:27.962
Then this information
was cross-referenced

49:28.463 --> 49:30.945
in multiple ways to
demonstrate its reliability

49:30.965 --> 49:33.948
and to show how it linked
with the 367 variables

49:33.968 --> 49:35.950
the study examined.

49:35.970 --> 49:37.952
I think the major message

49:37.972 --> 49:44.459
we got out of all these
correlation analyses

49:44.479 --> 49:47.462
is only one message.

49:47.482 --> 49:49.964
The plant food-based diet,

49:49.984 --> 49:53.968
mainly cereal grains,
vegetables, and fruits,

49:53.988 --> 49:57.472
and very little animal food

49:57.492 --> 50:03.978
is always associated with lower
mortality of certain cancers,

50:03.998 --> 50:07.982
stroke, and coronary
heart disease.

50:08.002 --> 50:09.984
The New York times called it

50:10.004 --> 50:12.987
"the most comprehensive
large study ever undertaken

50:13.007 --> 50:14.489
"of the relationship
between diet

50:14.509 --> 50:17.011
and the risk of
developing disease."

50:17.512 --> 50:21.496
For Dr. Campbell, he finally had
large-scale data on people,

50:21.516 --> 50:25.500
and it was remarkably consistent
with his earlier discoveries.

50:25.520 --> 50:30.505
Together, he found that the
scientific evidence was clear:

50:30.525 --> 50:34.008
Whole, plant-based foods were
beneficial to human health,

50:34.028 --> 50:36.530
while animal-based
foods were not.

50:44.038 --> 50:46.521
San'dera nation's journey
to better health

50:46.541 --> 50:49.023
wasn't easy at first.

50:49.043 --> 50:51.526
It was a little hard, 'cause
I'd been eating fatty foods

50:51.546 --> 50:55.029
and grease and
everything for 38 years,

50:55.049 --> 50:57.532
you know, as long
as I can remember,

50:57.552 --> 51:00.555
so it was kinda hard
to go from that

51:01.055 --> 51:04.038
to changing the next
day completely.

51:04.058 --> 51:07.542
I started a journal for maybe
the first three weeks,

51:07.562 --> 51:10.044
write down my feelings
and emotions,

51:10.064 --> 51:12.547
what I felt like...
So that other people

51:12.567 --> 51:15.550
could know it's okay
to feel that way.

51:15.570 --> 51:17.552
Along the way,

51:17.572 --> 51:20.555
San'dera had strong support
from Dr. Esselstyn

51:20.575 --> 51:22.557
and his wife Ann.

51:22.577 --> 51:25.059
They keep in touch,
and they're like,

51:25.079 --> 51:26.561
"we haven't forgotten
about you,"

51:26.581 --> 51:28.062
and I know they haven't.

51:28.082 --> 51:30.565
I really feel here
that they haven't.

51:30.585 --> 51:32.567
"I went to Wal-Mart this day.

51:32.587 --> 51:34.068
"I had wanted a subway sandwich,

51:34.088 --> 51:36.070
"and I said I'm gonna get
me that meatball sub.

51:36.090 --> 51:39.574
"I then received a call
while I was at Wal-Mart

51:39.594 --> 51:42.076
"from Mrs. Esselstyn,

51:42.096 --> 51:46.080
"as if they knew I was
weak at this moment.

51:46.100 --> 51:48.082
"She stated, 'promise me

51:48.102 --> 51:51.085
"you will not eat
anything from Wal-Mart.'

51:51.105 --> 51:53.588
"it gave me chills to know that
she called at that moment.

51:53.608 --> 51:55.590
"Therefore I left the store

51:55.610 --> 51:57.612
without getting
that meatball sub."

51:58.613 --> 52:00.114
What do you see?

52:00.615 --> 52:03.598
While Dr. Campbell was
publishing his China study,

52:03.618 --> 52:06.601
Dr. Esselstyn was getting
some powerful data

52:06.621 --> 52:09.604
from the research
he'd started in 1985.

52:09.624 --> 52:12.106
He began with 24 patients,

52:12.126 --> 52:15.109
but 6 had dropped out
in the first year,

52:15.129 --> 52:17.111
leaving him with a total of 18.

52:17.131 --> 52:20.615
At the end of five years, we
had follow-up angiograms,

52:20.635 --> 52:23.117
and 11 of the group had
halted their disease.

52:23.137 --> 52:24.619
There was no progression.

52:24.639 --> 52:28.623
And there were four where we
had rather exciting evidence

52:28.643 --> 52:30.625
of regression of disease.

52:30.645 --> 52:32.627
These results were astonishing.

52:32.647 --> 52:36.130
The diet produced something
that medication and surgery

52:36.150 --> 52:41.135
never had before: Actual
reversals of heart disease.

52:41.155 --> 52:44.639
The biological mechanism
that caused these reversals

52:44.659 --> 52:47.161
centers on the lining of
our veins and arteries...

52:47.662 --> 52:49.644
the endothelial cells.

52:49.664 --> 52:51.646
They are the absolute
life jackets

52:51.666 --> 52:53.147
of our blood vessels.

52:53.167 --> 52:56.150
You're young, and you're a
teenager, you're healthy,

52:56.170 --> 52:58.653
you could spread those
out one layer thick,

52:58.673 --> 52:59.654
and you'd have something
that would cover

52:59.674 --> 53:01.656
six or eight tennis courts.

53:01.676 --> 53:04.659
In 1988, scientists discovered

53:04.679 --> 53:06.160
that endothelial
cells manufactured

53:06.180 --> 53:08.663
the gas nitric oxide.

53:08.683 --> 53:11.165
Well, what did nitric oxide do?

53:11.185 --> 53:16.170
Nitric oxide keeps our
blood flowing smoothly

53:16.190 --> 53:18.172
without being sticky.

53:18.192 --> 53:21.175
It also helps to dilate
constricted blood vessels

53:21.195 --> 53:22.677
during physical activity

53:22.697 --> 53:25.680
and inhibits the
formation of plaque.

53:25.700 --> 53:29.684
And most importantly, nitric
oxide is a powerful force

53:29.704 --> 53:33.187
for eliminating the inflammation

53:33.207 --> 53:35.690
that seems to go
with this plaque.

53:35.710 --> 53:38.693
However, scientific
tests have demonstrated

53:38.713 --> 53:41.195
that when we start eating
the typical Western diet,

53:41.215 --> 53:44.699
our endothelial
cells are damaged.

53:44.719 --> 53:47.702
When you're getting to be in
your 40s and 50s and 60s,

53:47.722 --> 53:50.705
and you've been slaughtering
your endothelial cells,

53:50.725 --> 53:52.707
you don't have those six
or eight tennis courts.

53:52.727 --> 53:54.709
You may be down to one
and a half or two,

53:54.729 --> 53:56.711
and they can't protect you.

53:56.731 --> 53:59.213
Yet according to Dr. Esselstyn,

53:59.233 --> 54:02.717
when we begin eating a whole
foods, plant-based diet,

54:02.737 --> 54:05.720
the damage to our endothelial
cells not only stops,

54:05.740 --> 54:08.242
it starts to reverse.

54:16.250 --> 54:18.733
About five years into his study,

54:18.753 --> 54:21.235
Esselstyn made a small
but significant change

54:21.255 --> 54:22.737
in his patients' menu.

54:22.757 --> 54:25.239
It started in 1990,

54:25.259 --> 54:28.242
when he read the glowing review
of Dr. Campbell's China study

54:28.262 --> 54:31.245
the New York times.

54:31.265 --> 54:33.247
Dr. Esselstyn saw that,

54:33.267 --> 54:35.249
and he invited me to
come to a conference

54:35.269 --> 54:37.251
he was organizing in Arizona.

54:37.271 --> 54:39.253
These two revolutionaries,

54:39.273 --> 54:42.757
who, up until then, had been
on similar but separate paths

54:42.777 --> 54:46.260
finally met face-to-face.

54:46.280 --> 54:48.282
On the one hand, I'm coming
from the scientific group,

54:48.783 --> 54:50.264
getting some ideas.

54:50.284 --> 54:51.766
He's coming from
the clinical route

54:51.786 --> 54:54.769
and doing some
dramatic research.

54:54.789 --> 54:57.772
Here's the science, here's
the clinical evidence.

54:57.792 --> 54:59.273
Put the two together,
it's amazing.

54:59.293 --> 55:01.776
When he learned of
Campbell's research,

55:01.796 --> 55:06.280
Esselstyn removed dairy products
from his patients' diet.

55:06.300 --> 55:09.283
The results of his ongoing study
continued to be impressive,

55:09.303 --> 55:11.786
and in 1995, he
published a paper

55:11.806 --> 55:15.289
detailing them in a noted
scientific journal.

55:15.309 --> 55:18.793
Yet one of Esselstyn's most
remarkable success stories

55:18.813 --> 55:21.295
involved a colleague of his
at the Cleveland clinic,

55:21.315 --> 55:23.798
Dr. Joseph Crowe.

55:23.818 --> 55:27.802
Actually I was, um,
active, healthy,

55:27.822 --> 55:29.303
very busy,

55:29.323 --> 55:34.809
uh, mid-40s, absolutely,
um, no risk factors

55:34.829 --> 55:39.313
at all for any heart problem.

55:39.333 --> 55:41.816
But Dr. Crowe, even with
what was considered to be

55:41.836 --> 55:43.818
a healthy cholesterol level,

55:43.838 --> 55:46.821
was actually ravaged
by heart disease.

55:46.841 --> 55:48.823
This angiogram,

55:48.843 --> 55:52.326
taken after his first nearly
fatal heart attack in 1996,

55:52.346 --> 55:54.328
shows how badly damaged

55:54.348 --> 55:56.831
one of his coronary
arteries was.

55:56.851 --> 55:59.834
This angiogram was done
after less than three years

55:59.854 --> 56:02.356
of entirely dietary treatment.

56:09.363 --> 56:11.365
Dr. Crowe was fortunate.

56:11.866 --> 56:14.348
In 25% of cases, sudden death

56:14.368 --> 56:19.353
is the first and only sign
of coronary artery disease.

56:19.373 --> 56:23.357
Of Dr. Esselstyn's
original 18 patients,

56:23.377 --> 56:26.861
all survived the initial
12 years of the study.

56:26.881 --> 56:29.864
Today, 14 patients
are still alive

56:29.884 --> 56:33.367
over two decades after
the study began.

56:33.387 --> 56:37.371
The thing about essy, although
he's always very pleasant,

56:37.391 --> 56:40.374
when you said, "I'm going
to be on this program

56:40.394 --> 56:41.895
and I'm going to stay
with this diet,"

56:42.396 --> 56:44.879
you stayed with the diet,
or there was the door.

56:44.899 --> 56:46.380
You had no choice.

56:46.400 --> 56:50.384
I mean, his smiles
are wonderful,

56:50.404 --> 56:51.886
but he is very stern.

56:51.906 --> 56:53.888
You know, that's why
I'm still living.

56:53.908 --> 56:55.890
But, you know, he's just...

56:55.910 --> 56:59.894
He's just a wonderful man.

56:59.914 --> 57:00.915
And I look at the pictures...

57:01.415 --> 57:04.418
Some of my pictures
years ago, 20 years ago

57:04.919 --> 57:06.901
actually looks older than today.

57:06.921 --> 57:10.905
The only thing is I lost
more hair, you know?

57:10.925 --> 57:12.907
Anthony and the
other male patients

57:12.927 --> 57:14.408
also noted another change.

57:14.428 --> 57:15.910
When you're young,

57:15.930 --> 57:17.411
when you were teenager,

57:17.431 --> 57:22.416
you see a female or so on,
it gets kind of excited.

57:22.436 --> 57:25.419
And the first
reaction physically,

57:25.439 --> 57:27.922
you know, it gets
attention, you know?

57:27.942 --> 57:29.924
Raise the flag, I call it.

57:29.944 --> 57:33.928
This happened to us,
all the other, uh,

57:33.948 --> 57:37.431
Dr. Esselstyn's, uh, I call
'em all the Guinea pigs.

57:37.451 --> 57:40.434
The flag still rises.

57:40.454 --> 57:42.937
Talking to your doctor about e.D.

57:42.957 --> 57:44.939
May be the last
thing you wanna do,

57:44.959 --> 57:46.941
but it's definitely a
conversation worth having.

57:46.961 --> 57:48.943
I'm a practicing urologist

57:48.963 --> 57:51.445
and have been so for
the last 25 years.

57:51.465 --> 57:53.467
And erectile dysfunction
is actually

57:53.968 --> 57:55.950
the first clinical indicator

57:55.970 --> 57:59.453
of generalized
cardiovascular disease.

57:59.473 --> 58:01.455
It's the canary
in the coal mine.

58:01.475 --> 58:02.957
It's the thing
that lets you know

58:02.977 --> 58:05.479
that you have some
significant endothelial

58:05.980 --> 58:07.461
and vascular disease,

58:07.481 --> 58:10.464
much earlier than
will a heart attack

58:10.484 --> 58:11.966
or something like that.

58:11.986 --> 58:13.467
We have to stop
thinking of the body

58:13.487 --> 58:15.970
like it's compartmentalized.
It really isn't.

58:15.990 --> 58:18.472
The blood goes
everywhere in the body.

58:18.492 --> 58:21.995
And so if you have
vascular disease anywhere,

58:22.496 --> 58:24.979
you have it everywhere.

58:24.999 --> 58:28.482
Despite the apparent success
of the dietary approach,

58:28.502 --> 58:34.488
some critics say eating
this way is extreme.

58:34.508 --> 58:37.491
Now, with the Western diet,

58:37.511 --> 58:39.493
this guarantees there
are gonna be what?

58:39.513 --> 58:41.495
A half a million people
in this country this year

58:41.515 --> 58:45.499
who will have to have the front
half of their body divided,

58:45.519 --> 58:48.002
their heart exposed,

58:48.022 --> 58:50.504
then veins will be
taken from their leg

58:50.524 --> 58:52.006
and sewed on their heart.

58:52.026 --> 58:54.508
Some people would
call that extreme.

58:54.528 --> 58:58.031
Dr. Esselstyn has now
successfully treated

58:58.532 --> 59:01.015
over 250 patients
with heart disease,

59:01.035 --> 59:05.519
using almost exclusively a
whole foods, plant-based diet.

59:05.539 --> 59:07.021
Heart disease, as far
as I'm concerned,

