01:11:19.272 --> 01:11:20.253
They violated those.

01:11:20.273 --> 01:11:22.255
And we brought them to court,

01:11:22.275 --> 01:11:25.759
and it was a long
trial, but we won.

01:11:25.779 --> 01:11:27.260
But that doesn't change the fact

01:11:27.280 --> 01:11:28.762
that the policies
they came up with

01:11:28.782 --> 01:11:30.764
continued to favor industry
as they always have.

01:11:30.784 --> 01:11:33.266
I don't think there
really is a problem

01:11:33.286 --> 01:11:36.770
with industry connections
between scientists

01:11:36.790 --> 01:11:38.772
and the food industry,

01:11:38.792 --> 01:11:42.295
primarily because if
the beef industry

01:11:42.796 --> 01:11:44.778
has a question about
their products,

01:11:44.798 --> 01:11:48.281
shouldn't they go to
the best scientists?

01:11:48.301 --> 01:11:49.783
And if the best scientists

01:11:49.803 --> 01:11:52.285
are consulting for
the food industry,

01:11:52.305 --> 01:11:57.791
I still want the best
scientists on these committees

01:11:57.811 --> 01:11:59.793
that make nutritional
recommendations.

01:11:59.813 --> 01:12:01.795
Financial conflict of interest

01:12:01.815 --> 01:12:04.798
is only one conflict
of interest.

01:12:04.818 --> 01:12:05.799
You know, there are people

01:12:05.819 --> 01:12:07.801
who've spent their
entire careers

01:12:07.821 --> 01:12:11.805
trying to prove that a
vegetarian diet is good for you

01:12:11.825 --> 01:12:13.326
or that red meat is bad for you.

01:12:13.827 --> 01:12:15.809
Now, they may not
have industry ties,

01:12:15.829 --> 01:12:18.812
but they too have a
conflict of interest.

01:12:18.832 --> 01:12:21.314
You know, we do develop
biases personally.

01:12:21.334 --> 01:12:22.816
I had those biases, too.

01:12:22.836 --> 01:12:25.819
But I got to a
point in my career

01:12:25.839 --> 01:12:28.822
that I was getting results
that went against

01:12:28.842 --> 01:12:30.824
what I had thought was true.

01:12:30.844 --> 01:12:36.850
So I had to self-reflect,
criticize my own bias,

01:12:37.350 --> 01:12:38.832
look at it really carefully,

01:12:38.852 --> 01:12:40.834
and I changed my views.

01:12:40.854 --> 01:12:44.337
Dr. Campbell paid a price
for changing his views.

01:12:44.357 --> 01:12:45.839
He's been marginalized

01:12:45.859 --> 01:12:48.842
by key administrators
of his own university,

01:12:48.862 --> 01:12:50.844
this after being
a lead scientist

01:12:50.864 --> 01:12:53.346
and securing millions of
dollars in research grants

01:12:53.366 --> 01:12:56.349
for Cornell's nutritional
sciences division.

01:12:56.369 --> 01:12:58.351
He had a popular
nutrition course

01:12:58.371 --> 01:13:00.353
canceled by the
division director

01:13:00.373 --> 01:13:01.855
who had long been a
major consultant

01:13:01.875 --> 01:13:03.857
to the dairy industry.

01:13:03.877 --> 01:13:07.360
Numerous observers feel this
was an arbitrary decision

01:13:07.380 --> 01:13:10.363
that violated the standards
of academic freedom.

01:13:10.383 --> 01:13:14.367
Dr. Campbell has also witnessed
serious corporate influence

01:13:14.387 --> 01:13:15.888
over research that
is used to develop

01:13:16.389 --> 01:13:18.371
the government's
nutrition policy.

01:13:18.391 --> 01:13:20.874
One example he cites centers on

01:13:20.894 --> 01:13:23.877
the prestigious national
academy of sciences.

01:13:23.897 --> 01:13:26.379
The building behind
me here is perhaps

01:13:26.399 --> 01:13:28.901
the single most
important building

01:13:29.402 --> 01:13:30.884
in the area of science
in the country.

01:13:30.904 --> 01:13:33.887
This is where scientists
participate in deliberations

01:13:33.907 --> 01:13:35.388
about issues of the day

01:13:35.408 --> 01:13:39.412
and determine how that science
can be used to affect policy.

01:13:39.913 --> 01:13:41.394
In the early days
when I was involved,

01:13:41.414 --> 01:13:44.898
those panels were mostly
funded by public money.

01:13:44.918 --> 01:13:47.400
But on the other hand,
in more recent years,

01:13:47.420 --> 01:13:49.903
I have seen more and
more corporate money

01:13:49.923 --> 01:13:52.405
coming in to support
these activities

01:13:52.425 --> 01:13:55.408
and more and more people being
allowed on the committees,

01:13:55.428 --> 01:13:57.410
especially the chairs
of the committee.

01:13:57.430 --> 01:13:58.912
And, of course, they can
pick the kind of people

01:13:58.932 --> 01:14:00.413
they want to pick

01:14:00.433 --> 01:14:01.915
in order to get a certain
kind of conclusion.

01:14:01.935 --> 01:14:03.917
It's not the way it should be,

01:14:03.937 --> 01:14:05.919
and I'm sure that if the
public were to know

01:14:05.939 --> 01:14:09.943
how powerful is this influence,
they would be surely upset.

01:14:29.462 --> 01:14:31.464
I had been a runner
for 14 years,

01:14:31.965 --> 01:14:33.446
in fact, a marathoner.

01:14:33.466 --> 01:14:36.449
47 years old, the
top of my game.

01:14:36.469 --> 01:14:39.953
In 1982, Ruth heidrich's
running career

01:14:39.973 --> 01:14:40.954
came to a sudden stop

01:14:40.974 --> 01:14:43.456
when she was diagnosed
with breast cancer.

01:14:43.476 --> 01:14:47.460
After a mastectomy, her doctors
recommended chemotherapy

01:14:47.480 --> 01:14:48.962
and radiation to
treat the cancer

01:14:48.982 --> 01:14:51.965
that had by then spread
to her lungs and bones.

01:14:51.985 --> 01:14:55.468
Ruth decided to visit
Dr. John Mcdougall instead.

01:14:55.488 --> 01:14:57.971
And I said, "Ruth, I
spent my residency

01:14:57.991 --> 01:14:59.973
"collecting information on
diet and breast cancer.

01:14:59.993 --> 01:15:01.995
"It's all in these
files right here.

01:15:02.495 --> 01:15:03.977
"Sit in my office
and read through it

01:15:03.997 --> 01:15:04.978
and see what you think."

01:15:04.998 --> 01:15:07.480
He said, "these are the
studies that show...

01:15:07.500 --> 01:15:08.982
"what I'm trying to prove

01:15:09.002 --> 01:15:12.485
is that diet can reverse
breast cancer."

01:15:12.505 --> 01:15:14.487
And she read it,

01:15:14.507 --> 01:15:16.489
and she comes out and she says
"okay, I've changed my diet."

01:15:16.509 --> 01:15:17.510
She changed her diet.

01:15:18.011 --> 01:15:19.993
So he showed me how to eat.

01:15:20.013 --> 01:15:24.497
No added oils, lots of fruits
and vegetables, whole grains.

01:15:24.517 --> 01:15:26.499
Ruth then started training

01:15:26.519 --> 01:15:29.002
for the ironman
triathlon in Hawaii,

01:15:29.022 --> 01:15:31.004
which combines
running a marathon

01:15:31.024 --> 01:15:34.507
with long-distance
biking and swimming.

01:15:34.527 --> 01:15:36.509
I became obsessed.

01:15:36.529 --> 01:15:38.511
Kept up the running, of
course, never stopped,

01:15:38.531 --> 01:15:40.513
and then added swimming, biking,

01:15:40.533 --> 01:15:43.016
and, for good measure,
lifted weights.

01:15:43.036 --> 01:15:45.518
And people were saying,
"you're crazy.

01:15:45.538 --> 01:15:48.021
You're a cancer patient.
You should be resting."

01:15:48.041 --> 01:15:48.521
Doctors told me this.

01:15:48.541 --> 01:15:50.523
I felt so good.

01:15:50.543 --> 01:15:53.026
I felt fit, and I wanted to
maintain that level of fitness.

01:15:53.046 --> 01:15:56.029
And I felt sure that if
I had a healthy body

01:15:56.049 --> 01:15:58.531
and I was putting the
right food into it

01:15:58.551 --> 01:16:01.534
that I could beat this cancer.

01:16:01.554 --> 01:16:05.038
At the ironman triathlon,

01:16:05.058 --> 01:16:08.041
Ruth won a gold medal
in her age group.

01:16:08.061 --> 01:16:10.043
Stuck with the diet.

01:16:10.063 --> 01:16:12.045
Found out my arthritis
disappeared.

01:16:12.065 --> 01:16:14.047
My constipation disappeared.

01:16:14.067 --> 01:16:15.548
My dandruff disappeared.

01:16:15.568 --> 01:16:17.050
No sign of depression,

01:16:17.070 --> 01:16:19.572
which you might expect
with a cancer diagnosis.

01:16:20.073 --> 01:16:23.556
I felt renewed, invigorated,

01:16:23.576 --> 01:16:27.560
and out to show that diet
is so much more important

01:16:27.580 --> 01:16:30.063
than anybody ever thought.

01:16:30.083 --> 01:16:31.564
Mmm!

01:16:31.584 --> 01:16:33.066
Other women get
over breast cancer,

01:16:33.086 --> 01:16:35.068
colon cancer, prostate cancer.

01:16:35.088 --> 01:16:36.589
There are people who've had
metastatic prostate cancer

01:16:37.090 --> 01:16:38.571
all over their body

01:16:38.591 --> 01:16:40.593
who have gone through what we
call spontaneous remission.

01:16:41.094 --> 01:16:42.575
In other words,
they've been cured.

01:16:42.595 --> 01:16:43.576
And it's not the
end of the world

01:16:43.596 --> 01:16:45.578
when you get this diagnosis.
Some people get over it.

01:16:45.598 --> 01:16:46.599
Ruth did.

01:16:48.601 --> 01:16:50.583
So I'm still racing.

01:16:50.603 --> 01:16:52.585
Still daily training.

01:16:52.605 --> 01:16:55.588
Now how many people in their
70s are doing triathlons?

01:16:55.608 --> 01:16:57.090
Not very many.

01:16:57.110 --> 01:17:00.093
So that gives hope for
all of us as we age

01:17:00.113 --> 01:17:02.595
that not only will
you stay healthy

01:17:02.615 --> 01:17:06.599
and beat the degenerative
diseases that most people get,

01:17:06.619 --> 01:17:09.121
but you can start
collecting medals.

01:17:17.130 --> 01:17:19.112
The food choices we make

01:17:19.132 --> 01:17:21.134
have profound global effects.

01:17:24.637 --> 01:17:27.120
It takes over ten times
the amount of energy

01:17:27.140 --> 01:17:30.623
from fossil fuels to produce a
calorie of animal-based food

01:17:30.643 --> 01:17:33.626
than it does to produce a
calorie of plant food.

01:17:33.646 --> 01:17:37.630
Since the 1970s, 20% of
the Amazon's rainforest

01:17:37.650 --> 01:17:39.151
has been destroyed.

01:17:39.652 --> 01:17:42.635
That's an area the
size of California.

01:17:42.655 --> 01:17:47.640
80% of this cleared land is
now occupied by livestock.

01:17:47.660 --> 01:17:50.643
The world's cattle alone
eat enough grain to feed

01:17:50.663 --> 01:17:53.146
8.7 billion people,

01:17:53.166 --> 01:17:57.650
nearly 2 billion more than
the population on earth.

01:17:57.670 --> 01:17:59.652
With almost a billion
malnourished people

01:17:59.672 --> 01:18:03.156
across the globe, redirecting
even a portion of the grain

01:18:03.176 --> 01:18:05.658
used to fatten cattle could feed

01:18:05.678 --> 01:18:09.682
every hungry mouth
on the planet.

01:18:10.183 --> 01:18:13.666
For Gene Baur,
factors like these,

01:18:13.686 --> 01:18:15.668
combined with a deep
respect for animals,

01:18:15.688 --> 01:18:18.671
helped convince him to
adopt a plant-based diet.

01:18:18.691 --> 01:18:22.175
Mr. Baur is president and
co-founder of farm sanctuary

01:18:22.195 --> 01:18:24.677
near Watkins Glen, New York.

01:18:24.697 --> 01:18:27.180
It provides a safe
haven for animals

01:18:27.200 --> 01:18:29.682
that have been
abandoned or abused.

01:18:29.702 --> 01:18:33.186
I grew up eating animals like
most people in our country,

01:18:33.206 --> 01:18:36.689
but once I started
considering my food choices

01:18:36.709 --> 01:18:39.192
I recognized that I didn't
want to eat animals.

01:18:39.212 --> 01:18:42.695
And the more I learned,
the more I saw

01:18:42.715 --> 01:18:45.698
that I was healthier if
I didn't eat animals

01:18:45.718 --> 01:18:48.201
and that I had a much lighter
footprint on our planet.

01:18:48.221 --> 01:18:50.203
The livestock industry
is a greater contributor

01:18:50.223 --> 01:18:51.724
to global warming than the
entire transportation industry

01:18:52.225 --> 01:18:53.706
according to the United Nations.

01:18:53.726 --> 01:18:57.710
So by eating meat, milk,
and eggs the way we are,

01:18:57.730 --> 01:18:59.712
we're harming our own health,

01:18:59.732 --> 01:19:03.216
we're slaughtering 10
billion innocent animals

01:19:03.236 --> 01:19:04.217
every year in the U.S.,

01:19:04.237 --> 01:19:05.718
and we're destroying the planet.

01:19:05.738 --> 01:19:08.741
Statistics compiled
from the United Nations

01:19:09.242 --> 01:19:10.723
and the World
Health Organization

01:19:10.743 --> 01:19:12.725
demonstrate the
profound global effect

01:19:12.745 --> 01:19:15.228
that diet has on health.

01:19:15.248 --> 01:19:17.730
These are the estimated
amounts of animal foods

01:19:17.750 --> 01:19:19.732
produced in nine countries,

01:19:19.752 --> 01:19:23.736
a figure that's closely related
to animal food consumption.

01:19:23.756 --> 01:19:26.739
These are the numbers of deaths
due to heart disease and cancer

01:19:26.759 --> 01:19:29.261
in the same countries.

01:19:31.764 --> 01:19:33.246
In the United States,

01:19:33.266 --> 01:19:37.250
the very same diseases continue
to have a grave impact.

01:19:37.270 --> 01:19:38.751
Even with the
billions of dollars

01:19:38.771 --> 01:19:40.753
spent on cardiac treatment,

01:19:40.773 --> 01:19:43.756
heart disease is still the
number one cause of death,

01:19:43.776 --> 01:19:47.760
killing over 600,000
people a year.

01:19:47.780 --> 01:19:49.762
And the elephant in the room,

01:19:49.782 --> 01:19:53.266
when we talk about stents
and heart bypass surgery,

01:19:53.286 --> 01:19:55.788
is the fact that while
it's no question

01:19:56.289 --> 01:19:57.270
in an emergency,

01:19:57.290 --> 01:20:00.273
these procedures are
absolutely lifesaving.

01:20:00.293 --> 01:20:02.275
But when they're
done electively,

01:20:02.295 --> 01:20:06.279
these procedures do not protect
from new heart attacks.

01:20:06.299 --> 01:20:08.281
Stents and bypass operations

01:20:08.301 --> 01:20:10.783
are used mainly to treat
large arterial blockages.

01:20:10.803 --> 01:20:14.787
Yet according to many
research studies,

01:20:14.807 --> 01:20:16.789
only a small percentage
of heart attacks

01:20:16.809 --> 01:20:19.792
are caused by the largest
build-ups of plaque.

01:20:19.812 --> 01:20:22.795
The rest are caused by the
more numerous, newer blockages

01:20:22.815 --> 01:20:24.297
that are far more inflamed

01:20:24.317 --> 01:20:26.299
and much more likely to rupture

01:20:26.319 --> 01:20:30.303
than the larger, older,
more stable plaques.

01:20:30.323 --> 01:20:33.306
And so this is why
those procedures

01:20:33.326 --> 01:20:34.807
don't treat the disease.

01:20:34.827 --> 01:20:36.328
They are treating symptoms.

01:20:38.331 --> 01:20:41.314
Doctor Esselstyn has been
eating the same foods

01:20:41.334 --> 01:20:45.818
that he has recommended to his
patients for over 25 years.

01:20:45.838 --> 01:20:49.822
One of his sons, Rip Esselstyn,
used a plant-based diet

01:20:49.842 --> 01:20:51.824
to fuel a successful
ten-year career

01:20:51.844 --> 01:20:53.345
as a professional tri-athlete.

01:20:53.846 --> 01:20:57.349
When Rip turned 34, he was
ready for a career change

01:20:57.850 --> 01:21:00.352
and trained to become
a firefighter.

01:21:05.358 --> 01:21:07.840
Rip was assigned to
engine company number 2

01:21:07.860 --> 01:21:09.842
in Austin, Texas.

01:21:09.862 --> 01:21:13.346
We're incredibly competitive
here at the fire station,

01:21:13.366 --> 01:21:14.847
and we love making bets.

01:21:14.867 --> 01:21:16.849
So we were out on the
porch one night,

01:21:16.869 --> 01:21:18.851
and we kind of made
this little bar bet

01:21:18.871 --> 01:21:20.853
to see who had the lowest
cholesterol level.

01:21:20.873 --> 01:21:24.857
So the next morning, we
drove to a lab, got tested,

01:21:24.877 --> 01:21:26.859
and the results came back.

01:21:26.879 --> 01:21:29.862
And it lead to a
discovery that J.R.,

01:21:29.882 --> 01:21:33.866
James Ray, our resident redneck,
had a cholesterol of 344.

01:21:33.886 --> 01:21:36.369
Pretty much means you're
knocking at death's door.

01:21:36.389 --> 01:21:39.872
And so what we did, in
an act of solidarity,

01:21:39.892 --> 01:21:43.876
is the next day we went about
eating a plant-strong diet,

01:21:43.896 --> 01:21:46.398
to basically save his life
and save his arteries.

01:21:46.899 --> 01:21:49.902
The men agreed to change
their firehouse diet.

01:21:50.403 --> 01:21:53.886
But in Texas, old
eating habits die hard.

01:21:53.906 --> 01:21:56.389
Meat's almost a sport in Texas.

01:21:56.409 --> 01:21:58.891
I have several good friends
that, they're barbeque teams.

01:21:58.911 --> 01:21:59.892
That's what they do.

01:21:59.912 --> 01:22:01.894
That's their sport on weekends.

01:22:01.914 --> 01:22:03.396
Texans are serious
about their barbeque.

01:22:03.416 --> 01:22:04.917
Texas, Kansas.

01:22:14.927 --> 01:22:18.911
Well, guys associate being
manly with eating meat.

01:22:18.931 --> 01:22:21.414
And if you're a firefighter,
it's exponentially so.

01:22:21.434 --> 01:22:26.919
Last year, for example, there
were 133 firefighter fatalities

01:22:26.939 --> 01:22:28.421
in the United States.

01:22:28.441 --> 01:22:32.425
52% were from heart disease.

01:22:32.445 --> 01:22:35.928
Our number one killer of
in-the-line-of-duty deaths

01:22:35.948 --> 01:22:37.930
for firefighters
is heart disease.

01:22:37.950 --> 01:22:40.433
After just three weeks
on his new diet,

01:22:40.453 --> 01:22:42.935
j.R.
Tested his blood cholesterol,

01:22:42.955 --> 01:22:47.440
and it dropped 148 points,
a decrease of 43%.

01:22:47.460 --> 01:22:49.942
His results inspired the others,

01:22:49.962 --> 01:22:51.944
who also saw their
cholesterol drop

01:22:51.964 --> 01:22:54.447
and their energy levels rise.

01:22:54.467 --> 01:22:57.450
As firemen, they were not
only helping themselves,

01:22:57.470 --> 01:23:00.953
they were in better
shape to assist others.

01:23:00.973 --> 01:23:02.455
One of the things about
being a firefighter

01:23:02.475 --> 01:23:04.957
is you don't have any idea
what your next call could be.

01:23:04.977 --> 01:23:06.959
We may have a high-rise alarm,

01:23:06.979 --> 01:23:09.462
where we have to go up
20 flights of stairs

01:23:09.482 --> 01:23:10.963
with air packs on,

01:23:10.983 --> 01:23:12.465
with all of our bunker gear on,

01:23:12.485 --> 01:23:14.967
with a high rise
pack on our backs.

01:23:14.987 --> 01:23:16.969
Anybody can go down the poll,

01:23:16.989 --> 01:23:19.972
but not everybody can go up,
especially without their legs.

01:23:19.992 --> 01:23:22.975
And right there
you're talking about

01:23:22.995 --> 01:23:25.978
an additional 75 to 100 pounds

01:23:25.998 --> 01:23:27.480
that you have to carry
up 20 flights of stairs.

01:23:27.500 --> 01:23:29.482
You have to have an
amazing aerobic capacity

01:23:29.502 --> 01:23:30.983
and strength in
order to do that.

01:23:31.003 --> 01:23:34.987
Real...Men...Eat...Plants.

01:23:35.007 --> 01:23:38.991
Real...Men...Eat...Plants.

01:23:41.013 --> 01:23:43.496
You know what, as firefighters,

01:23:43.516 --> 01:23:46.999
everybody thinks that we
fight fire, and we do.

01:23:47.019 --> 01:23:50.503
But over 70% of our calls
are medical emergencies

01:23:50.523 --> 01:23:54.006
where we are responding
to heart disease,

01:23:54.026 --> 01:23:58.010
hypertension, type 2
diabetes, rampant obesity.

01:23:58.030 --> 01:24:01.514
And so we see, up
close and personal,

01:24:01.534 --> 01:24:03.516
basically the destruction
that's being caused

01:24:03.536 --> 01:24:05.538
by the standard American diet.

01:24:06.038 --> 01:24:07.539
To me, the answer

01:24:08.040 --> 01:24:10.523
is just absolutely so
simple, it's criminal.

01:24:10.543 --> 01:24:13.025
